Having graduated from medical school, Scott Carter, a fair-skinned African American, marries Marsha Mitchell and moves to Georgia. Discussions between two nurses at this clinic suggest that Scott's light skin may have some bearing on the decision not to hire him. Defeated but not conquered, Scott returns to Massachusetts to live with his in-laws until he can get employment. He tries unsuccessfully to obtain employment as an African American. Because Marsha is pregnant, Scott decides to take a job at Portsmouth Hospital, but he reluctantly does so as a white man. While there, he manages to save the life of Dr. Bracket, who encourages him to take a postion in Keenham, New Hampshire. Scott decides to continue "passing" for white. In Keenham, Dr. Scott Carter proves to be quite a success for the town. For twenty years, Dr. and Mrs. Carter live peacefully in Keenham with son, Howard and daughter, Shelley. All goes well until Scott and Howard decide to enter the military during World War II. When Scott applies for officer status with the Navy, an investigation reveals his black heritage, and he is barred from receiving a commission.

desc1: In 2017, a successful businessman travels to the ends of the earth to find that the perfect woman is always under his nose. He hires a sexy renegade tracker to find an exact duplicate of his android wife.

Title: 7676. Maharshi
desc1: A story about Rishi and his quest for success in different stages of life from being a US-based businessman to being a champion for the poor downtrodden farmers.

Title: 7677. Mortdecai
desc1: Juggling angry Russians, the British Mi5, and an international terrorist, debonair art dealer and part-time rogue Charlie Mortdecai races to recover a stolen painting rumored to contain a code that leads to lost gold.

Title: 7678. Love in the Villa

Title: 7679. CBGB
desc1: A look at the New York City punk-rock scene and the venerable nightclub, CBGB.

Title: 7680. Nobody's Fool
desc1: A stubborn man past his prime reflects on his life of strict independence and seeks more from himself.

Title: 7681. Mafia Wars
desc1: An ex-con gets released early from prison only to be forced into an undercover unit of six men and on his first day the other five are all killed. Now he must face the men who he was tasked to spy on.

Title: 7682. The Shakedown
desc1: When his mistress threatens to expose the secret of their affair, a respectable insurance broker seeks the help of his underworld brother to save his reputation.

Title: 7683. The Neighbor
desc1: A middle-aged man in a stagnant marriage finds his life upended when an attractive young woman and her seemingly abusive husband move in next door.

Title: 7684. So Undercover
desc1: A tough, street-smart private eye is hired by the FBI to go undercover in a college sorority.

Title: 7685. Coolie
desc1: Delves into a man's relentless quest for vengeance since youth, driven by righting past wrongs, shaping his very existence. Viewers experience the complexities of his tumultuous vendetta journey.

Title: 7687. Fanboys
desc1: Star Wars fanatics take a cross-country trip to George Lucas' Skywalker Ranch so their dying friend can see a screening of Star Wars: Episode I - The Phantom Menace (1999) before its release.

Title: 7688. Swimfan
desc1: A high school senior with a promising swimming career has a one-night stand with consequences.

Title: 7689. The Prince of Tides
desc1: A troubled man talks to his suicidal sister's psychiatrist about their family history and falls in love with her in the process.

Title: 7690. Beneath the Valley of the Ultra-Vixens
desc1: Believe it or not, even Smalltown USA still has people who are unfulfilled and unrelieved in the midst of plenty. Levonna and Lamar could have the perfect relationship, were it not for Lamar's obsession with rear entry.

Title: 7691. A Mistake
desc1: In the midst of a new scheme to publicly report surgeons' performance, a gifted surgeon's life is thrown into disarray as her colleagues begin to close ranks, and even her partner who is a nurse at the hospital turns her back on her.

Title: 7692. Twister
desc1: Delusional and spoiled Maureen and her eccentric brother Howdy decide to track down and meet their estranged mother, all while the drama of dysfunctional relationships, disastrous weather conditions and a dark family secret ensue.

Title: 7693. An Awkward Sexual Adventure
desc1: To win back his ex-girlfriend, a conservative accountant enlists the help of an exotic dancer to guide him on a quest for sexual experience, leading him into a world of strip clubs, sensual massage parlors, cross-dressing and S & M.

Title: 7694. Mo' Money
desc1: A con man, seeking to gain the affections of a woman he saw entering an office building, aquires a job in the same building working for an executive who has plans to use his skills for more than just the workplace.

Title: 7695. Point Blank
desc1: After being double-crossed and left for dead, a mysterious man named Walker single-mindedly tries to retrieve the money that was stolen from him.

Title: 7696. Rehnaa Hai Terre Dil Mein
desc1: Maddy impersonates Rajeev, the person his love interest, Reena, is about to marry and attempts to woo her. However, he is unprepared for the moment when the truth will be revealed.

Title: 7697. Afternoon Delight
desc1: Rachel tries to spice up her marriage with a trip to a strip club. She befriends McKenna, who gave her a lapdance. McKenna moves in with Rachel's family and becomes a nanny for the son.

Title: 7698. The Survivalist
desc1: In a time of starvation, a survivalist lives off a small plot of land hidden deep in forest. When two women seeking food and shelter discover his farm, he finds his existence threatened.

Title: 7699. The Man Who Killed Don Quixote
desc1: Toby, a disillusioned film director, is pulled into a world of time-jumping fantasy when a Spanish cobbler believes himself to be Sancho Panza. He gradually becomes unable to tell dreams from reality.

Title: 7700. Belle
desc1: Suzu is a shy high school student living in a rural village. For years, she has only been a shadow of herself. But when she enters "U", a massive virtual world, she escapes into her online persona as Belle, a globally-beloved singer.

Title: 7701. Mercury Rising
desc1: Shadowy elements in the NSA target a nine-year old autistic savant for death when he is able to decipher a top secret code.

Title: 7702. Hop
desc1: E.B., the Easter Bunny's teenage son, heads to Hollywood, determined to become a drummer in a rock 'n' roll band. In LA, he's taken in by Fred after the out-of-work slacker hits E.B. with his car.

Title: 7703. 24 Hour Party People
desc1: In 1976, Tony Wilson sets up Factory Records and brings Manchester's music to the world.

Title: 7704. Omni Loop
desc1: A woman from Miami, Florida decides to solve time travel in order to go back and be the person she always intended to.

Title: 7705. Z
desc1: The public murder of a prominent politician and doctor amid a violent demonstration is covered up by military and government officials. A tenacious magistrate is determined not to let them get away with it.

Title: 7706. Dream House
desc1: Soon after moving into their seemingly idyllic new home, a family learns of a brutal crime committed against former residents of the dwelling.

Title: 7707. Tragedy Girls
desc1: A twist on the slasher genre, following two death-obsessed teenage girls who use their online show about real-life tragedies to send their small mid-western town into a frenzy, and cement their legacy as modern horror legends.

Title: 7708. The Blood on Satan's Claw
desc1: In early 18th century England, the children of a village slowly convert into a coven of devil worshipers.

Title: 7709. Speak No Evil
desc1: When all the children in a small town become possessed, one mother refuses to believe that her daughter is lost to the devil and will do whatever it takes to keep her alive.

Title: 7710. Wonder Boys
desc1: An English Professor tries to deal with his wife leaving him, the arrival of his editor who has been waiting for his book for seven years, and the various problems that his friends and associates involve him in.

Title: 7711. Just Cause
desc1: A Harvard professor is lured back into the courtroom after twenty-five years to take the case of a young black man condemned to death for the horrific murder of a child.

Title: 7712. The Idiots
desc1: The group of people gather at the house in Copenhagen suburb to break all the limitations and to bring out the "inner idiot" in themselves.

Title: 7713. On an Island with You
desc1: While shooting on location in the South Pacific, a movie star is pursued by a handsome Naval officer who is convinced she is the girl for him.

Title: 7714. Disconnect
desc1: A drama centered on a group of people searching for human connections in today's wired world.

Title: 7715. The Good Neighbor
desc1: A pair of mischievous high school kids create the illusion of a haunting on an unsuspecting elderly neighbor while keeping his every reaction under surveillance. A series of coincidences leads to tragedy.

Title: 7716. Hardware
desc1: The head of a cyborg reactivates, rebuilds itself, and goes on a violent rampage in a space marine's girlfriend's apartment.

Title: 7717. The Trial
desc1: An unassuming office worker is arrested and stands trial, but he is never made aware of his charges.

Title: 7718. R.I.P.D. 2: Rise of the Damned
desc1: Recruited by the R.I.P.D., a resurrected sheriff returns to Earth to save humanity from a gateway to hell.

Title: 7719. Bloodbath at the House of Death
desc1: Six scientists investigate a strange phenomenon at the creepy Headstone Manor, the site of a mysterious massacre years earlier that took the lives of 18 guests in one night.

Title: 7720. Alarum
desc1: Two rogue spies go off-grid, marry, and come under attack at their remote cabin hideaway by various intel agencies seeking a stolen hard drive.

Title: 7721. Lady Jane
desc1: The story of Lady Jane Grey, who was Queen of England for only nine days.

Title: 7722. Nick and Norah's Infinite Playlist
desc1: Two newly acquainted music-lovers spend the night scouting the streets of New York City in search of their favourite band's surprise secret show. All the while, they're both being chased after by their tempting but devious exes.

Title: 7723. Out of the Blue

She calls on Arthur while his wife is out, and when she passes out during his attempts to get her out before his wife returns, he thinks she is dead and deposits her on Galleo's terrace. Galleo takes advantage of the situation by using it in a blackmail scheme against Arthur, which is shaky, at best, as Olive refuses to stay dead.

Title: 7724. Calendar Girls
desc1: Best friends Chris and Annie are members of a charitable institute. When Annie's husband succumbs to leukemia, the friends decide to pose nude for a calendar to raise funds for a local hospital.

Title: 7725. Saturn 3
desc1: Two lovers stationed at a remote base in the asteroid belt of Saturn are intruded upon by an anal-retentive technocrat from Earth and his charge: a malevolent eight foot tall robot.

Title: 7726. Estômago II: O Poderoso Chef
desc1: Nonato, with his food, won over the powerful in the hierarchy of the prison where he is serving his sentence. But the arrival of a famous Italian mobster will shake the structures and place the chef at the epicenter of a power struggle.

Title: 7727. The Moogai
desc1: A young Aboriginal couple brings home their second baby. What should be a joyous time takes a sinister turn, as the baby's mother starts seeing a malevolent spirit she is convinced is trying to take her baby.

Title: 7728. Somewhere Quiet
desc1: Follows a woman as she readjusts to normalcy after a kidnapping. Her sense of reality begins to deteriorate when she travels to her husband's family compound.

Title: 7729. Bad Education
desc1: An examination on the effect of Franco-era religious schooling and sexual abuse on the lives of two longtime friends.

Title: 7730. Ghost Town
desc1: Bertram Pincus is a man whose people skills leave much to be desired. When Pincus dies unexpectedly, but is miraculously revived after seven minutes, he wakes up to discover that he now has the annoying ability to see ghosts.

Title: 7731. Book of Shadows: Blair Witch 2

Title: 7732. Escape Plan: The Extractors
desc1: After security expert Ray Breslin is hired to rescue the kidnapped daughter of a Hong Kong tech mogul from a formidable Latvian prison, Breslin's girlfriend is also captured.

Title: 7733. The Final Conflict
desc1: The now adult Antichrist plots to eliminate his future divine opponent while a cabal of monks plot to stop him.

Title: 7734. The Housemaid
desc1: A man's affair with his family's housemaid leads to dark consequences.

Title: 7735. Behind the Candelabra
desc1: A chronicle of the tempestuous six-year romance between megastar singer Liberace and his young lover Scott Thorson.

Title: 7736. The Burning Sea
desc1: An oil platform dramatically goes down on the Norwegian coast, and researchers try to find out what happened when they realize this is just the start of something even more serious.

Title: 7737. Live Flesh
desc1: After leaving jail, Víctor is still in love with Elena, but she's married to the former cop -now basketball player- who became paralysed by a shot from Víctor's gun...

Title: 7738. AKA
desc1: A steely special ops agent finds his morality put to the test when he infiltrates a crime syndicate and unexpectedly bonds with the boss's young son.

Title: 7739. Cosmopolis
desc1: Riding across Manhattan in a stretch limo in order to get a haircut, a 28-year-old billionaire asset manager's day devolves into an odyssey with a cast of characters that start to tear his world apart.

Title: 7740. I'm Your Man
desc1: In order to obtain research funds for her studies, a scientist accepts an offer to participate in an extraordinary experiment: for three weeks, she is to live with a humanoid robot, created to make her happy.

Title: 7741. Blonde Venus
desc1: A cabaret singer takes up with a millionaire to pay for her gravely-ill husband's operation.

Title: 7742. The Petrified Forest
desc1: A waitress, a hobo and a bank robber get mixed up at a lonely diner in the desert.

Title: 7743. Earthquake
desc1: Various interconnected people struggle to survive when an earthquake of unimaginable magnitude hits Los Angeles, California.

Title: 7744. The Current War
desc1: The dramatic story of the cutthroat race between electricity titans Thomas A. Edison and George Westinghouse to determine whose electrical system would power the modern world.

Title: 7745. Kon-Tiki
desc1: In 1947, with five loyal friends in tow, explorer Thor Heyerdahl sails a fragile balsa wood raft along an ancient path some 4,300 miles across the Pacific.

Title: 7746. Conviction
desc1: A working mother puts herself through law school in an effort to represent her brother, who has been wrongfully convicted of murder and has exhausted his chances to appeal his conviction through public defenders.

Title: 7747. Some Freaks
desc1: A charming romance develops between a boy with one eye and an overweight girl, though when she loses her weight after going to college, their relationship is tested in devastating ways they never dreamed would happen.

Title: 7748. Bedspacer
desc1: Janice's steamy obsession to imitate Lexi propels them to campus stardom. But dark secrets blur the lines between authenticity and seductive deception.

Title: 7749. Wish Dragon
desc1: Determined teen Din is longing to reconnect with his childhood best friend when he meets a wish-granting dragon who shows him the magic of possibilities.

Title: 7750. Liquid Sky
desc1: A small, heroin-seeking UFO lands on a Manhattan roof, observes a bizarre, drug-addicted fashion model, and sucks endorphin from her sexual encounters' brains.

Title: 7751. Love & Friendship
desc1: Lady Susan Vernon takes up temporary residence at her in-laws' estate and, while there, is determined to be a matchmaker for her daughter Frederica--and herself too, naturally.

Title: 7752. How to Plan an Orgy in a Small Town
desc1: When "town slut" turned sex columnist Cassie Cranston returns for her mother's funeral it spices things up in the small town of Beaver's Ridge when a group of eccentric town folk, each with their own motives, convince her to plan an orgy.

Title: 7753. White Men Can't Jump
desc1: A remake of the 1992 film about a pair of basketball hustlers who team up to earn extra cash.

Title: 7754. Our Almost Completely True Story
desc1: A statuesque Hollywood icon meets a Jewish leprechaun in a bird store--what are the chances?

Title: 7755. District B13
desc1: Captain Damien must team up with Leito, a local insurgent from District 13, to defuse a neutron bomb that has fallen into the hands of a local drug lord, Taha, and rescue Leito's sister Lola.

Title: 7756. An Unfinished Life

Title: 7757. We Were Dangerous
desc1: Nellie, Daisy and Lou attend an institution for delinquent girls on an isolated island in 1954. The trio rail against the system, finding strength in their friendship but this is challenged when the school's matron divides them.

Title: 7758. Blue Steel
desc1: A rookie in the police force must engage in a cat-and-mouse game with a pistol-wielding psychopath who becomes obsessed with her.

Title: 7759. Chopping Mall
desc1: A group of young shopping mall employees stay behind for a late night party in one of the stores. When the mall goes on lock-down before they can get out, the robot security system malfunctions, and goes on a killing spree.

Title: 7760. Out Cold
desc1: A snowboarder's plans for his own snowboard park go awry when an ex-girlfriend returns to town.

Title: 7761. Hostage
desc1: When a family is held hostage, former hostage negotiator Jeff Talley arrives at the scene. Talley's own family is kidnapped and Talley must decide which is more important: saving a family he doesn't even know or saving his own family.

Title: 7762. Joe Versus the Volcano
desc1: When a hypochondriac learns that he is dying, he accepts an offer to throw himself in a volcano at a tropical island, and along the way there, learns to truly live.

Title: 7763. A New York Story
desc1: A young woman risks being ostracized from an insular New York clique led by her socialite best friend when she falls for a charming photographer.

Title: 7764. Sorority Row
desc1: A group of sorority sisters try to cover up the death of their house-sister after a prank gone wrong, only to be stalked by a serial killer.

Title: 7765. Losin' It
desc1: Set in 1965, four rowdy teenage guys travel to Tijuana, Mexico for a night of partying when they are joined by a heartbroken housewife who is in town seeking a quick divorce.

Title: 7766. Rock 'n' Roll High School
desc1: Ramones fanatic and delinquent Riff Randell battles it out with the strict new principal of Vince Lombardi High School, Miss Togar, with help from the Ramones.

Title: 7767. Step Up Revolution
desc1: Emily arrives in Miami with aspirations to become a professional dancer. She sparks with Sean, the leader of a dance crew whose neighborhood is threatened by Emily's father's real estate development plans.

Title: 7768. You Got Served
desc1: In order to achieve their dream of opening a recording studio, two friends (Omarion, Houston) must first win their city's dance contest -- a fierce competition that pits them against a group of tough street dancers.

Title: 7769. Windfall
desc1: A man breaks into a tech billionaire's empty vacation home, but things go sideways when the arrogant mogul and his wife arrive for a last-minute getaway.

Title: 7770. The Perfect Game
desc1: Based on a true story, a group of boys from Monterrey, Mexico who became the first non-U.S. team to win the Little League World Series.

Title: 7771. A Soldier's Story
desc1: An African-American officer investigates a murder in a racially charged situation in World War II.

Title: 7772. Head-On
desc1: With the intention to break free from the strict familial restrictions, a suicidal young woman sets up a marriage of convenience with a forty-year-old addict, an act that will lead to an outburst of envious love.

Title: 7773. The Wandering Earth
desc1: With the sun dying out, a group of brave astronauts set out to find new planet for the whole human race.

Title: 7774. My Summer of Love
desc1: In the Yorkshire countryside, working-class tomboy Mona meets the exotic, pampered Tamsin. Over the summer season, the two young women discover they have much to teach one another, and much to explore together.

Title: 7775. 13 Sins
desc1: A cryptic phone call sets off a dangerous game of risks for Elliot, a down-on-his-luck salesman. The game promises increasing rewards for completing 13 tasks, each more sinister than the last.

Title: 7776. Mother's Day
desc1: Three generations come together in the week leading up to Mother's Day.

Title: 7777. Blue Hawaii
desc1: After arriving back in Hawaii from the Army, Chad Gates defies his parents' wishes for him to work at the family business and instead goes to work as a tour guide at his girlfriend's agency.

Title: 7778. Cowboy Bebop: The Movie
desc1: A terrorist explosion releases a deadly virus on the masses, and it's up to the bounty-hunting Bebop crew to catch the cold-blooded culprit.

Title: 7779. The High Note
desc1: A superstar singer and her overworked personal assistant are presented with a choice that could alter the course of their respective careers.

Title: 7780. Alone in the Dark
desc1: A detective of the paranormal slowly unravels mysterious events with deadly results.

Title: 7781. F/X
desc1: A movie special effects man is hired to fake a real-life mob killing for a witness protection plan, but finds his own life in danger.

Title: 7782. The Great Raid
desc1: Taking place towards the end of WWII, 500 American Soldiers have been entrapped in a camp for 3 years. Beginning to give up hope they will ever be rescued, a group of Rangers goes on a dangerous mission to try and save them.

Title: 7783. Unicorn Wars
desc1: War-hungry teddy bears journey from bootcamp to the psychedelic terrors of the Magic Forest in this darkly beautiful horror animation.

Title: 7784. Hippopotamus
desc1: Ruby has been kidnapped, but her kidnapper doesn't want a ransom. He wants her to fall in love with him.

Title: 7785. Angela's Ashes
desc1: An Irish Catholic family returns to 1930s Limerick after a child's death in America. The unemployed I.R.A. veteran father struggles with poverty, prejudice and alcoholism as the family endures harsh slum conditions.

Title: 7786. Tampopo
desc1: A truck driver stops at a small family-run noodle shop and decides to help its fledgling business. The story is intertwined with various vignettes about the relationship of love and food.

Title: 7787. Yoga Hosers
desc1: Two teenage yoga enthusiasts must do battle with an evil presence that is threatening to rise from its underground lair and endanger their major party plans.

Title: 7788. The Entertainment System Is Down
desc1: Set on a long-haul flight where the entertainment system fails, the film will see passengers forced to face the horror of being bored.

Title: 7789. Eyes Without a Face
desc1: A surgeon causes an accident which leaves his daughter disfigured and goes to extreme lengths to give her a new face.

Title: 7790. Boy
desc1: Boy, an 11-year-old child and devout Michael Jackson fan who lives on the east coast of New Zealand in 1984, gets a chance to know his absentee criminal father, who has returned to find a bag of money he buried years ago.

Title: 7791. Hamburger Hill
desc1: A very realistic interpretation of one of the bloodiest battles of the Vietnam War.

Title: 7792. A Little Romance
desc1: American teenager Lauren King living in Paris, meets and falls in love with a local boy named Daniel Michon. They befriend storyteller Julius and take a trip to Venice in George Roy Hill's romantic comedy.

Title: 7793. Kidnapped: The Abduction of Edgardo Mortara
desc1: A Jewish boy is kidnapped and converted to Catholicism in 1858.

Title: 7794. Lakeview Terrace
desc1: A troubled and racist African-American L.A.P.D. Officer will stop at nothing to force out a friendly interracial couple who just moved in next door to him.

Title: 7795. Opening Night
desc1: A renowned actress teeters on the edge of a breakdown as she counts down the days toward a big Broadway opening.

Title: 7796. The Believer
desc1: A young Jewish man develops a fiercely anti-Semitic philosophy. Based on the factual story of a K.K.K. member in the 1960s who was revealed to be Jewish by a New York Times reporter.

Title: 7797. Loser
desc1: A college student, branded a loser by his roommates and booted from the dorm, falls in love with a coed who has eyes for their condescending professor.

Title: 7798. Maniac Cop
desc1: A killer dressed in a police uniform begins murdering innocent people on the streets of New York City.

Title: 7799. Journey to the Center of the Earth
desc1: An Edinburgh professor and assorted colleagues follow an explorer's trail down an extinct Icelandic volcano to the earth's center.

Title: 7800. The Rite
desc1: American seminary student Michael Kovak travels to Italy to take an exorcism course.
